1. [COMPLETED] Rich Text Formatting in Text Fields — Implemented Tiptap rich text editor with markdown storage for ALL multiline text fields: description, assumption, evidence, Project Context, and Tree Context. Toolbar with Bold, Italic, Underline, Bullet List, and Ordered List (appears on focus only). Keyboard shortcuts (Cmd+B/I/U) supported. Auto-save with debounce works for assumption/evidence; explicit Save button for context fields. Fixed race condition in RichTextEditor (isProgrammaticRef suppresses onChange during programmatic setContent). No backend changes needed (markdown stored as plain text).

1.1 [COMPLETED] Markdown formatting on graph viewer — Description text on canvas node bubbles now renders markdown (bold, italic, lists) via shared markdownToHtml utility. Title remains plain text. Extracted markdownToHtml to shared lib/markdown-to-html.ts used by both OSTNode and InlineEditableText.

2. [COMPLETED] Edge Line Styling — Slider Thickness + Dashed/Dotted Lines. Replaced the 6-button thickness menu with a smooth slider (range 1-20, step 0.5) with live preview bar. Added dashed and dotted line style options with SVG previews and teal active-state highlighting. Edge thickness changed from int to float in backend. New edge_style column (VARCHAR 20) added to nodes table with auto-migration. Menu stays open after adjustments so users can change both thickness and style in one interaction. Changes persist across page refreshes. CLI updated with --edge-thickness (float) and --edge-style options. All 347 tests pass.

3. [COMPLETED] Multi-Assumption Management with 3-State Status Toggle — Transformed the single assumption/evidence text fields into a multi-assumption model. Each node can now have multiple assumption+evidence pairs via a new `node_assumptions` table. Each assumption has a 3-state status toggle (untested → confirmed → rejected) displayed as a clickable checkbox with green checkmark (confirmed), red X (rejected), or empty (untested). Cards have colored borders/backgrounds matching status. Rich text editors with 800ms debounced auto-save. Rejected assumptions have disabled editors and reduced opacity. Canvas nodes show assumption counts by status (e.g., "1 ✓ 2 untested 1 ✗"). Header shows breakdown: "(1 confirmed, 1 untested, 1 rejected)". Empty state shows "No assumptions yet. Click + Add to create one." Export/import preserves assumption status. Snapshots include assumptions. Validation warns about missing assumptions. Chat integration: add_assumption, update_assumption, reject_assumption tools. CLI: `ost assumption add/list/update/reject/delete` commands. SQLite migration handles both fresh DB creation and existing data migration. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean.

4. [COMPLETED] Activity Tab Condensation — When consecutive activity entries share the same summary text, they are now condensed into a single row showing the most recent entry with a "×N" count badge. The badge tooltip shows "N identical changes condensed" and the time tooltip shows the full time range of the group. Clicking a condensed entry still navigates to the relevant node. The condensation respects the All/Mine filter — filtering happens first, then condensation runs on the filtered results. Frontend-only change in ActivityPanel.tsx; no backend changes needed. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean.

5. [COMPLETED] Chat Persistence Bug Fix — Chat now persists across fold/unfold, page reloads, AND tree/project switches. Original fix: Changed chat ResizablePanel to use `collapsible` + `collapsedSize={0}` so the component stays mounted when collapsed. Added `PanelImperativeHandle` ref for programmatic expand/collapse, `onResize` callback to sync Zustand store state. Follow-up fix: Added frontend-side chat history save for error cases (when the backend chat API fails, e.g., no API key configured, the backend never reaches its save code). New `POST /trees/{tree_id}/chat-history` endpoint saves messages from the frontend. ChatPanel.tsx error handler now persists user message + error response to DB so they survive tree switches. Chat history loads from DB on mount via `chat-history` API. Messages persist until actively discarded via "Clear history" button. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean.

6. [COMPLETED] Edge Color — Grey Tone Configuration. Added edge_color property across the full stack. Right-click any edge to open the context menu which now includes a "Color" section with 10 grey tone swatches (Default + grey-100 through grey-900). Active swatch highlighted with teal border and scale effect. Lighter swatches have subtle inner shadow for visibility against white background. Preview bar in thickness section reflects current edge color. New edge_color column (VARCHAR 20) on nodes table with auto-migration. Export/import preserves edge color. CLI updated with --edge-color option. Changes persist across page reloads. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean.

7. [COMPLETED] Auto-create first assumption + bubble display improvements — Every non-outcome node (opportunity, child_opportunity, solution, experiment) now automatically gets one empty assumption card on creation. Backend: `add_node()` in tree_service.py auto-creates an empty assumption via `repo.add_assumption(node.id, NodeAssumptionCreate())`. Import: when importing nodes that already have assumptions, the auto-created one is removed first to avoid duplicates; nodes with no assumptions in import data keep the auto-created empty one. Frontend: NodeDetailPanel has a `useEffect` that auto-creates an assumption for existing non-outcome nodes with 0 assumptions (ref-guarded to fire once per node). Canvas bubbles: empty assumptions (no text) are excluded from assumption counts so auto-created but unfilled cards don't clutter the badge. OSTNode badge: removed "untested" word, now shows just the blue number. Outcome nodes are excluded from auto-assumption. CLI/Chat use `service.add_node()` so they get the auto-assumption automatically. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean.

8. [COMPLETED] Remove the feedback functionality (UI on the right side). Feedback will be collected in different ways. Removed: FeedbackButton component + directory, feedback API router, html2canvas dependency, .feedback storage directory. Updated layout.tsx and main.py. All tests pass, TypeScript clean.

9. [COMPLETED] Detail View Toggle — Canvas nodes expand to show full content (description, assumptions with status + evidence). "Detail" toggle button added below "Compact" in the top-left control panel, using the same highlight style. When active, nodes expand to 460px wide with: colored node-type badge (OUTCOME, OPPORTUNITY, SOLUTION, etc.), index number, full title, divider line, DESCRIPTION section with full markdown-rendered text, ASSUMPTIONS section with status counts (confirmed/untested/rejected), and individual assumption cards showing status indicator + assumption text + evidence in a 2-column layout. Cards are color-coded: green border for confirmed, red for rejected, neutral for untested. Nodes without content (no description, no filled assumptions) stay compact. Layout uses wider spacing (480px node width, 320px height, 60px sibling gap, 420px rank separation) via parameterized layout functions. Auto-fitView animation on toggle. Read-only rendering — no editing in canvas view. Frontend-only change across OSTNode.tsx, TreeCanvas.tsx, tree-store.ts, and tree-layout.ts. No backend changes needed. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean.

10. [COMPLETED] Remove Open Mode: Always Require Authentication — On a fresh database the app previously entered "open mode" with no login screen and no auth required, with no UI path to create a user account. Fixed by: (1) Auto-generating OST_JWT_SECRET via secrets.token_hex(32) and persisting to .env if not configured, so registration works out of the box. (2) Removing the open-mode bypass from get_current_user_required() in deps.py — always requires a valid Bearer token now. (3) /auth/status always returns auth_required: true; user_count still returned so frontend knows which tab to default to. (4) Login page fetches user_count on mount and defaults to "Create Account" tab when user_count === 0, "Sign In" when users exist; removed the authRequired === false redirect bypass. (5) Main page auth check simplified to just if (!isAuthenticated) — auth is always required. (6) check_project_permission() now raises PermissionDeniedError("Authentication required") when user_id is None instead of silently returning; single-user implicit-owner bypass kept. (7) API tests updated with client_authed fixture that registers a user and auto-injects Bearer tokens; all test classes switched to use it. RBAC tests updated: TestOpenMode now verifies user_id=None raises PermissionDeniedError. (8) Cleaned up "open mode" references across comments in use-permissions.ts, MembersSection.tsx, TreeSelector.tsx, projects.py, CLI main.py. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean.

11. [COMPLETED] Child Nodes Vertically Squashed When Sibling Node Is Tall — Added content-aware height estimation to the tree layout algorithm in `tree-layout.ts`. New `estimateNodeHeight()` function predicts rendered pixel height from node data (title length, description, tags, assumptions) for both compact and expanded modes. Both `layoutWide` and `layoutCompact`/`computeSubtree` now use `Math.max(rs, parentEstimatedHeight + MIN_GAP)` per parent node, where MIN_GAP=40px. This ensures tall nodes (long descriptions, many assumptions, detail-mode expansion) get proportionally more vertical space to their children, while short/simple nodes keep the standard rank separation as a floor. Height estimation accounts for markdown rendering (newline-based line counting for bullet lists), border widths, assumption card inter-gaps (space-y-1.5), and conservative chars-per-line estimates to prevent overlaps. Single file change: `frontend/src/lib/tree-layout.ts`. Works in all 4 view modes (normal, compact, detail, detail+compact). No backend changes. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean.

12. [COMPLETED] Settings Persistence to .env + Free-Text Model Input — Replaced hardcoded model dropdown with a free-text input field (saves on blur or Enter). Removed `PROVIDER_MODELS` dict and `provider_models` from API response. All settings (model, provider, API keys) now persist to `.env` file via new `persist_to_env()` helper in config.py (reuses pattern from `_ensure_jwt_secret()`). Runtime overrides still set for immediate effect; `.env` write ensures survival across server restarts. Updated help text from "stored in server memory only" to "saved to .env file on the server". Frontend SettingsDialog uses `<Input type="text">` for model with placeholder example. TypeScript interface updated to remove `provider_models`. No CLI changes needed. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean. Verified via Playwright: model input works, API key saves, provider persists, and all values survive full server restart.

13. [COMPLETED] Add delete_assumption tool to chat — Added `delete_assumption` tool definition in `llm/tools.py` and handler in `chat.py` so the AI can permanently remove assumptions when users ask. Calls existing `service.delete_assumption()`. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean.

14. [COMPLETED] Dynamic Skills Loading for Chat Agent — Replaced the static 40-line SKILLS_REFERENCE in the system prompt with tool-based on-demand loading. Added `list_skills` tool (scans docs/skills/, returns names + descriptions from YAML frontmatter) and `read_skill` tool (returns full file content). System prompt now just has a short note saying skills are available via tools. Agent reads full skill content only when methodology questions arise. Fully dynamic — drop a new .md file in docs/skills/ and it's immediately discoverable. Skills directory contains: OKR (MIT, marfoerst), OST + Discovery Process + Discovery Interview Prep (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, Dean Peters). ATTRIBUTION.md included. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean.

15. [COMPLETED] Fix fold level toolbar not tracking manual node expansions — The `-` button in the toolbar was disabled when `visibleDepth === 0` even if nodes had been manually expanded via the round indicators (expandedBeyondDepth set was non-empty). Fixed by adding `&& expandedBeyondDepth.size === 0` to the disabled condition so the `-` button stays enabled when manual expansions exist. Also added `Level 0+/3` display format (the `+` suffix) to indicate manual expansions are active beyond the global depth. Clicking `-` now correctly collapses manual expansions stage-by-stage before the button becomes truly disabled. Single-line fix in TreeCanvas.tsx. All tests pass, TypeScript clean. Verified via Playwright: collapse to 0, manually expand, toolbar `-` works to fold back in.

16. [COMPLETED] Real-Time Streaming Tool Indicators in Chat — Replaced the static "Thinking..." loading indicator with real-time streaming tool activity labels. Backend: New `POST /chat/stream` SSE endpoint yields `tool_start`, `tool_end`, and `done` events as the agentic loop processes tool calls. `_tool_display_label()` helper maps tool names to human-friendly labels (e.g., "Getting tree...", "Validating tree...", "Reading skill: Opportunity Solution Tree..."). Shared `_build_system_prompt()` and `_check_chat_permission()` helpers extracted to reduce duplication between streaming and non-streaming endpoints. System prompt included in `done` event for expanded view. Frontend: `api.chat.sendStream()` method uses `fetch()` + `ReadableStream` to parse SSE events via callbacks. `ToolActivityIndicator` component shows animated dots + tool label with 150ms fade transitions. `ChatPanel` uses streaming by default with fallback to non-streaming on failure. `activeTools` state tracks in-progress tools with unique instance IDs (handles duplicate tool names). Stream abort on component unmount, tracked setTimeout cleanup via `toolEndTimersRef`. Stale label flash on re-entry fixed via `prevLoadingRef`. Tool badges (get_tree, validate_tree, list_skills, read_skill, etc.) still appear on final messages as before. No emojis in indicators. All 347 tests pass, TypeScript clean.